author: lgo
msg: When retrying a request after an Authorization Required response, make sure
the second request is added at the beginning of the request queue, before any
unwritten requests waiting on that queue.
This helps ensuring that requests aren't sent out of order when using NTLM
newly added serf_connection_priority_request_create in serf, falls back to
non-priority with older versions of serf.
(handle_response): when retrying the request after a 401 response, add it
add the start of the outgoing request queue.
